The paper presents a new family of priors for Bayesian learning of tree belief networks, which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the integration of factored distributions over spanning trees in a graph, which is a topic related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new class of tractable latent variable models, which is a topic related to statistical inference and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the computation of likelihoods through ensemble averages, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT).
